<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="across-prep">across <strong><em>prep</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /əˈkrɒs/    美 /əˈkrɔːs/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>(从一边到另一边) 横过；穿过：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>walk across the bridge / street / road
过桥/街/马路</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>France is Europe’s third largest country and faces the United Kingdom across the English Channel.
法国是欧洲第三大国家，隔英吉利海峡与英国相望。</p><footer>外研③ – 1</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Do you think this shirt is too tight across the shoulders?
你觉得这衬衫的肩部是不是太紧了？</p><footer>2012 北京</footer></div>

<h3 id="across-through">辨析 across , through</h3>
<p>二者都有“穿过”的意思。<br />
<strong>across</strong>  指横过，表示动作从一边到另一边沿物体的表面进行。
**through ** 指从中间穿过，表示动作在某立体空间中进行。</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It took us hours to walk through the forest.
我们费了几个小时才穿过森林。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>在…另一边；在…对面：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>At the front door stood a five-year-old boy from across the street. 
前门站着一个来自街对面的5岁男孩。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.<strong>从 / 在 / 到...各处：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Nelson Mandela is respected and admired across the world.
纳尔逊·曼德拉在世界各地受到尊重和敬仰。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>He suddenly saw Sue <strong><em>_</em></strong><em> the room. He pushed his way <strong><em>_</em></strong></em> the crowd of people to get to her.  <br />
A.across; across<br />
B.over; through<br />
C.over; into<br />
D.across; through  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. D  </p></div>